[[File:Bronze armour set (lg) equipped.png|thumb|130px|A player with bronze armour equipped.]]
'''Bronze equipment''' are items made from [[Metal#Basic metals|bronze metal]]. Bronze equipment is the weakest equipment in ''[[RuneScape]]''. All bronze items are coloured brown. Bronze armour requires 1 [[Defence]] to wield, weapons require 1 [[Attack]].

==Weapons==
'''Bronze weapons''' require an [[Attack]] level of 1 to wield.

===One-handed melee weapons===
{{Infotable Bonuses|Bronze dagger#(unp)|Bronze axe|Bronze mace|Bronze sword|Bronze longsword|Bronze scimitar|Bronze hasta#(unp)|Bronze warhammer|Bronze battleaxe|Bronze pickaxe|sort=str|nototals=yes}}

===Two-handed melee weapons===
{{Infotable Bonuses|Bronze claws|Bronze spear#(unp)|Bronze 2h sword|Bronze halberd|sort=str|nototals=yes}}

===Ranged weapons and ammo===
{{Infotable Bonuses|Bronze crossbow|Bronze bolts#Unpoisoned|Bronze arrow#(unp)|Bronze brutal|Bronze dart#(unp)|Bronze javelin#Unpoisoned|Bronze thrownaxe|Bronze knife#(unp)|sort=rstr|nototals=yes}}

==Armour==
'''Bronze armour''' is the lowest quality [[armour]] in the standard spectrum of metal armours ([[Bronze equipment#Armour|bronze]] to [[Dragon equipment#Armour|dragon]]). Bronze armour requires 1 [[Defence]] to wear.

{{Infotable Bonuses|Bronze med helm|Bronze full helm|Bronze chainbody|Bronze platebody|Bronze platelegs|Bronze plateskirt|Bronze sq shield|Bronze kiteshield|Bronze boots|Bronze gloves|Bronze defender#Normal|sort=dslash|nototals=yes}}

==Other==
[[Bronze trimmed armour|Trimmed]] and [[Bronze gold-trimmed armour|gold-trimmed]] bronze armour have the same bonuses as standard bronze armour. These can be obtained from the member's only [[Treasure Trails]] minigame.

'''Note:''' Other players '''''cannot''''' trim or bless armour. Players claiming to do so are scammers.

